description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of United Lincolnshire Hospitals NHS Trust’s commitment to meeting the health care needs of the local population, applications are invited for the post of an LAS ST3 in Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics at Pilgrim Hospital, Boston.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is a 10 PA basic (additional APAs by prior agreement and subject to regular review) middle-grade post with duties undertaken primarily at Pilgrim Hospital with regular clinics at peripheral sites including Grantham. The appointee will be responsible for the management of elective and emergency patients and would be expected to be able to perform most orthopaedic procedures under supervision. The post-holder will be assigned to a Consultant but should be prepared to work as required within the Department. There is a 1 in 12 on-call commitment with prospective on-call cover for the other non-training middle-grade surgeons. Although this post is not recognised for training it could prove useful to candidates who have completed basic surgical training and wish to acquire hands-on surgical experience while awaiting a Specialist Registrar appointment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have at least three years medical work post registration with at least 12 months experience in Orthopaedic Surgery. A post-graduate qualification in Surgery/Orthopaedic Surgery is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTheo joachimJob titleOrthopaedic surgeonEmail addresstheophilus.joachim@ulh.nhs.ukTelephone number01205) 445674Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mrs Chloe Scruton, Deputy General Manager, telephone number (01522) 573040.&lt;/p&gt;
